{"title": "Noiseless Walker", "content": "Walking isn't a silent action. It can be a loud, elephant-like sound or graceful steps. But people still make some noise when they walk. Except this character.\n\nMeet the Noiseless Walker. For some reason, his steps are completely silent. This character may have ninja-like skills, or something magical in their nature which negates the sound of walking. It may be used to show he's a badass for managing to move around without people noticing him, or to establish an alien or otherwordly nature because the absence of a natural sound often looks off.\n\nOr perhaps he just uses artificial means such as a noise-cancelling suit or spell. Such cases are likely to be temporary, unless moving silently is a character's whole shtick.\n\nThis trope is one of the most plausible reasons for managing a Stealth Hi/Bye (the other being Offscreen Teleportation). See With Catlike Tread for when this trope fails.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoiselessWalker", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/HunterXHunter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MissionYozakuraFamily", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Asterix", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ArtemisFowl", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBelgariad", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheHobbit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLordOfTheRings", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/RangersApprentice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheVoyageOfTheDawnTreader", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/XandriCorelel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KungFu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Seinfeld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/DungeonsAndDragons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Toys/Bionicle", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Bioshock", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DeusExHumanRevolution", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DeusExMankindDivided", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheElderScrollsVSkyrim", "/pm